# Inventory the transport/policy split

## Step

Standing call: the existing gateway daemon survives as dumb transport; the agent owns all policy. This step produces the file-level split of `packages/gateway/` (plus `packages/message-contract/` and the notify path through `packages/sdk/` and `packages/cli/`).

For each module, classify:

- **transport (keeps)**: Chat SDK adapters, single-poller ownership, platform normalization, delivery mechanics, receipts, journaling.
- **policy (moves to the agent)**: kinds routing, delivery modes, batching, digest assembly, suppression, formatting profiles, telegram-outbound-policy.
- **seam (changes shape)**: the `send()` boundary, notify-compat shim, inbound event publication.

Note where the priority-lane removal (`.brain/projects/messaging-stabilization/follow-up-remove-priority-lanes.svx`, implemented 2026-07-19) already moved things, so this effort doesn't fight that one. Also identify the minimal change that makes the fallback real: transport delivering raw text to Telegram when the agent heartbeat is stale — which existing code path is closest to that?

Resolved when an asset (`asset-transport-policy-split.svx`) lists every relevant file with its classification and the fallback path recommendation. Feeds [Design the fallback contract](./design-fallback-contract.svx).
